Tom Ryan, 40, was struck by a Toyota while making deliveries on Staten Island . 
  He was crushed against his own truck and left with one leg hanging by a thread . 
  Onlookers used a shirt as a tourniquet in a desperate attempt to stop the bleeding . 
  Mr Ryan was 'screaming in agony' but is expected to live . 
  Toyota driver told police he swerved to avoid a jaywalker . 
 